                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/224.]</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Legation</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Minister of Panama has called at the Department to urge intercession by this
                    Government in behalf of Eloy Alfaro. Dietrich reports that Alfaro and Páez are
                    being taken to Quito for trial. While this Government fully realizes that it
                    would be inappropriate to make formal representations, it feels nevertheless
                    that a recurrence <pb facs="0515" n="399" xml:id="pg_399"/> of such a brutal
                    lynching as occurred at Guayaquil might be unfortunate for the good name of
                    Ecuador.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
